<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-42-0117 </DOCNO><TEXT>Mine surveying technology has been revolutionised during recent yearswith the introduction of automated systems of data measurement, acquisition,processing and plotting. The technology required for completely automatingthe whole survey process is already available. This paper outlines theapplication of the automated survey system used by the Department ofMining Engineering, University of Nottingham to the measurement of subsidenceover a longwall face together with details of the results obtained. 5refs., 7 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>